				<main role="main" class=""><article class="main-content"><h1 class="">Lukfata Public School<br>
</h1>
        <div class="pom-container">
            <h2 class="">Soaring with Excellence: Today, Tomorrow, and Always</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="">Welcome to the online home of Lukfata Public School! Located in southeastern
            Oklahoma, along the foothills of the Kiamichi Mountains in McCurtain County,
            our school is known for its academic excellence and community support.
            Serving over 300 students in prekindergarten through 8th grade, we are
            pleased to offer our families a well-rounded curriculum and a highly
            qualified, caring staff.</p>
        <p class="">We invite you to browse our website to learn more about our outstanding school.
            If you have any questions, feel free to stop by or give us a call. If
            you ever notice anything inaccurate or outdated on the website, please <a href="mailto:jsundberg@lukfata.org" title="" alt="" target="_top" class="">let us know</a>. </p>
        <h2 class="">A Message from Our Superintendent</h2>
        <p class=""><img src="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_291292/site_291294/Graphics/Staff_KurtNeal.jpg" alt="Portrait of Superintendent Kurt W. Neal" class="" style="max-width: 118px; width: 35%; margin: 10px 0px 10px 10px;" align="right">Welcome to Lukfata Public Schools! I would like to take a moment to express,
            on behalf of all the staff at Lukfata, our desire to partner with you
            in your child's education. We understand that mere knowledge can
            be taught anywhere, but true education can only happen as a partnership
            among family, school, and community, with each voice respecting and
            encouraging the others. That is why we infuse character education into
            every aspect of our curriculum, encouraging our students to participate
            in extra-curricular activities and sports, and providing opportunities
            for you—our parents and community members—to join us by volunteering
            in the classroom and visiting our campus during community nights.</p>
        <p class="">We appreciate all you do to support us in our endeavors here at Lukfata.
            Thanks to you, our excellent staff, and our hard-working students, <a href="https://www.oklaschools.com/" title="" alt="" target="_blank">our
            state report card</a> only reiterated
            what we already knew—Lukfata Falcons Soar! We look forward to continuing
            that reputation with you and soaring with excellence throughout the years
            to come!</p>
            <p class=""> Sincerely,</p>
            <p class="signature">Kurt W. Neal</p>
            <p class=""><a href="mailto:kneal@lukfata.org" title="" alt="" target="_top">Kurt W. Neal</a>,
                Superintendent</p>
            <div class="pom-container">
                <h2 class="">A Message from Our Principal</h2>
                <div class="pom-container">
                    <p class="">Dear Parents and Guardians,</p>
                    <p class=""><img src="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_291292/site_291294/Graphics/Staff_ClintGlasson.jpg" alt="Portrait of Principal Clint Glasson" class="" align="right" style="max-width: 118px; width: 100%;">Welcome to Lukfata Elementary School. We are proud of our dedicated,
                        experienced staff and enthusiastic learners!</p>
                    <p class="">As demands and complexities of teaching children increase, it
                        becomes more evident that we all need to work together to
                        insure that our children reach their potential. We believe
                        it is everyone’s responsibility to empower children with
                        the creative, intellectual, and decision-making skills necessary
                        for them to become academically, socially, physically, and
                        emotionally successful and responsible.</p>
                    <p class="">With that in mind, I invite you to be an active participant at
                        Lukfata School. Research clearly demonstrates
                        that parent participation in their child’s school coincides
                        with a greater likelihood that the child will academically succeed.</p>
                    <p class="">If you have questions or concerns that arise at any time, please
                        do not hesitate to give your child’s teacher or me a call.
                        I look forward to having a long and rewarding relationship
                        with you and your family.</p>
                     <p class="">Sincerely,</p>
                        <div class="pom-container">
                            <p class="signature">Clint Glasson</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="pom-container signature">
<span style="color: rgb(13, 36, 68); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;" class=""><a href="mailto:cglasson@lukfata.org" title="" alt="" target="_top">Clint Glasson</a>, Principal</span>
                        </div>
                </div>
            </div>
